SUPER EASY bear muffins! 🧸 
from @annabelkarmel “Fun, Fast & Easy” children cooking book

Ingredients : 
1 - 1/4 cup self rising flour 
1/2 tsp baking powder 
2oz superfine sugar 
1/2 tsp ground cinnamon 
1/2 tsp ground ginger 
4oz sunflower oil 
2 - 1/2 oz maple syrup 
2 medium eggs , lightly beaten 
1/2 tsp vanilla extract 
1 apple peeled , cored and grated 
2- 1/2 oz carrots , peeled and grated 
1- 1/2 oz raisins 

Instructions: 

•preheat the oven to 350F and line a 12 hole muffin tin with paper cases. 
•Measure the flour , baking powder, sugar , cinnamon, and ginger into a large mixing bowl. 
•combine the oil , maple syrup, eggs, and vanilla in a separate large bowl and beat lightly with a whisk until blended. 
•Add the grated apple, carrots , and raisins to the liquid mixture, then fold in the dry ingredients until just combined . Be careful not to over mix. 
•Fill the muffin cases until two thirds full and bake in the oven for 20-25 min. 
•Remove from the oven and leave to cool in the pan for 5 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely. 

For decoration: 
Make your muffins into mini bears- slice an apricot in half for ears, place a whole apricot with a raisin on top of the nose, then finish with some edible eyes. 

We can’t wait to see you making this fun recipe! ❤️
don’t forget to tag me and @annabelkarmel

Wanted to posted a smoothie that I often feature on my stories and always get DMs about the proportions💜
 
Not long ago, I started to incorporate protein smoothies into my diet after workouts , just feels like a great way to add the extra protein in. 
I know protein shakes can’t substitute a meal - but on days when you don’t have time & choice,  it feels like better than nothing kind of a thing. 

For 1 portion: 
•frozen banana 
•1 cup of any frozen berries (I love to use sour cherries) 
•1/2 cup of any non sweeten vegan milk (I use almond from @elmhurst1925 , you can also add more if you want a smoothie to be more liquid) 
•1 teaspoon of any nut butter 
•2 scoops of protein powder (I use vegan one from @sproutliving , and also it’s unflavored, which I find like a big plus, so it doesn’t overpower the taste of fruits) 
•1 teaspoon of vanilla extract

My love for skiing did not grow from beautiful Courchevel with it’s stunning alps & Michelin star restaurants. 💫
It really all started in Khabarovsk (that’s where I’m from) at the age of 7, that’s when I did my first run down some local hills - don’t know their name 😂
I remember us going with my parents every weekend to the local skiing resort that was nothing close to Courchevel haha 🫠
We skied all day at -30C (-22F) & 
had a picnic outside, eating burned potatoes from a bone fire & shashlik (shish-kebob)😂. But my favorite part was always the walnut shaped cookies with dolce de leche filling. It was a reward & something I was looking forward to after morning of freezing my butt & not feeling my toes anymore 😂
 A lot has changed in those 20 years but love for skiing stayed the same ❤️
Wait for the last picture…..😂 lol

Paris Travel Guide🇫🇷 

Before my Paris trip I did a Q&A asking for Paris recommendations! I received tonsss of them! And of course in just a week, I wasn't able to visit all of them.  But I decided to share the places that have been mentioned the most ❤️

•Arpège - seasonal fine dining, my personal FAVORITE in Paris, every trip I make sure I have a meal there. 

•Girafe - beautiful place with a view on the Eiffel tower and good food. 

•Loulou- restaurant with a terrace, great at summer time. 

•Cafe de l’homme - great food & view on the Eiffel Tower. 

•Sinner - party & restaurant place 

•Hotel Costel 

•L’Avenue- trendy place especially during FW, food is good. 

•Ora - Vegetarian restaurant. 

•Passage 53 - Japanese chef cooking French with a lot of Asian influence. 

•Epicure at Le Bristol- for classic perfectly executed food, very upscale place 

•Les Caves Augé - wine shop. 

This trip we managed to get tickets for
 •Crazy Horse- which was super fun and super sexy! 
•Moulin Rouge was sold out unfortunately 🫠 still on my bucket list! 
 
We stayed in JKPlace hotel , which we absolutely loved- very cosy & great location. 

Lmk if I guys forgot anything good?

Ah….and almost forgot, make sure to check out my new Paris VLOG, I attached link in bio ☺️👆🏻

Here are some more photos from my pregnancy shoot 🤍 (those are not the photos I’m talking about bellow lol) 

Fun fact: I never told anyone- not even my husband 😂 but when I was pregnant with Allegra, I also did a pregnancy shoot towards the end of my pregnancy. A photographer reached out to me through friends, and her work looked good, so I agreed. 

During the shoot, I quickly realized how complicates the concept was—it involved a lot of decor, props, and lighting. Having worked in the industry for a while, I knew how challenging it can be to execute something so complex.

When I received the pictures, they turned out to be a total fail 🫠 The styling, the lighting - everything was wrong! It was the first time in my life that I had to ask a photographer not to post the photos. I felt bad about it, but fortunately, she took it well 😅 Now, looking back, I see this situation as less dramatic than I did back then 😂 I even thought about sharing those photos with you (not mentioning the photographer🙈) so we could have a good laugh together? 😂

Yesterday, when I was asked if I ever get jealous of my husband's beautiful exes, I replied that I'm not jealous- I'm proud, haha. He's dated many, but he chose me. I received a few feedbacks one of which was, that I shouldn't give a man the power to make it sound like he chose me-  in her view (person who wrote me) it was all in the context of women empowerment. 

However, what I was really trying to say is the truth….My husband was the first to notice me, to reach out, to invite me on a date, to propose, and to discuss our future together…and that’s exactly the way I invisioned it for myself.  In this era of "women's empowerment," where traditional tales of prince come to concure the princess as seening something wrong…and traditional values of family as seeing someone is not appropriate. 

Let me clarify, I'm all for supporting women in business, motherhood, sisterhood, and any other aspect of life. But being a strong woman, in my view, doesn't mean I have to emulate stereotypical male qualities in every aspect of my life. I'm personally  comfortable being feminine and gentle when I'm with my husband. It's the place where I can be my true feminine self

For me, independence isn't about refusing help from a man or letting him be a man. it's about having my own independence of thought, interests, and opinions. It's not a competition between genders. 

As a mother of girl(s) in this modern world, I hope to instill in them the idea that being a strong doesn't always mean taking the lead in everything. It's about having the sensibility and intuition to know when to step up and when to step down…

📖Mom Diary: It’s been a strange week, full of different events and emotions. 
On Thursday- as Allegra came back from school, I noticed she was acting out, and as I tend to be strict, I went straight into disciplining her. After 30 minutes of arguments, I asked her if there was something she needed to tell me. I told her I could see something was bothering her inside. She burst into tears, saying, ‘Mommy, a baby is coming, and you won’t have time for me,’ which made me burst into tears too.🤪😅 (yeah I’m supper hormonal) 
It didn’t come out of nowhere. I was busy all week organizing the baby’s room and her room as well, and I was off our usual routine of driving to school together and picking her up. What seemed unnoticeable to me felt like a big deal for her…

We ended up having a dance party in her room that day and laying on her bed, discussing all the fun things we will do once the baby is born, like playing active games, for example , or rollerblading. I assured her that no matter how busy I am, I will always make sure we have those special moments just the two of us. When you think they are still little and don’t connect the dots just yet….they are not that little anymore. 
As much as I’m excited for the new baby, I’ve also been overwhelmed with a good amount of anxiety about the upcoming change…

Meeting my sister for the FIRST time…🥹

Before I share my birth story, let’s just appreciate this special moment and think about the odds of being born on the same day as your sister? 🙏🏻🥹 I’m sobbing watching this video! 
Becoming the mother of two is truly one of the best things that happened to me—it expands your heart in a way you never thought possible.

It also tests your nerves and resilience, ahah! Let me tell you! This month has been rough—adjusting to a new role, accepting that two babies are completely different, and realizing that what worked for Allegra won’t work for Aurora. Trust me, I thought I had it all planned and knew everything!

Whatever plans you make before birth are truly going to be thrown out of the window—so my advice for new moms is to go with the flow!

But one thing I can admit for sure, the second time around, I notice a much more peaceful state of my mind. I prioritize ME a lot over anything—over friends, over my husband, over my kids! Because I know it’s important to take care of ME—so I don’t fall into the same hole of postpartum. I take breaks if I need to, accept help, take A LOT of naps, and don’t rush to get back to work (that’s why I’ve been missing for one month). It hasn’t been easy to let go a bit, but the thought that I won’t be able to relive this special moment again with my little ones kept me in the right place with my mind and heart! ❤️

It’s been one month! One month of pure joy with two of my babies—happy little birthday, Aurora

I’m proud of us @valeriomorabito ❤️
